$ SAS: syntax check mode
@ syntax check mode

If not prevented by setting → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/syntaxcheck[nosyntaxcheck], SAS enters *syntax check mode* whenever a syntax error occurs in a → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/data-step (except `_null_` data steps) or
a → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/proc[proc step].

Entering syntax check mode causes to set → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/obs to 0 and
→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/replace[noreplace].

sa:
  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/syntaxcheck,
  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/dmssyncheck

sa:
  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming
